description.0: When Howard finds himself possessed, he uses his new power to free him and Winda from the mental hospital. Enraged by his power, Howard leaves Winda behind and flies to Cleveland to find Beverly. But what he discovers may be the beginning of the end!?
description.1: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.2: Robinson Crusoe flees England and sets sail for a new life course! But a horrific shipwreck lands Crusoe on a faraway island, with little chance of survival. Adapting the classic novel!
description.7: It's the adaptation of A New Hope!   Meet Luke Skywalker, Princess Leia, Obi-Wan and the villianous Darth Vader!
description.8: Spider-Man under the 'hypnotic' charm of Dr. Faustus! After Spidey uncovers Faustus' sinister plot, the wall-crawler is made to believe that his worst enemies are on his trail! Faustus has a master plan that will leave residents of New York City under a hallucinogenic trance. Will Spider-Man snap out of it in time to save the day?
description.9: Ant Man has been acting strangely lately, much to the concern of Wasp. Will Hank Pym's erratic behavior be the undoing of the Avengers? Introducing Yellowjacket!
description.10: Captain America battles tooth and nail against the entity called Nazi X!
description.11: Intrigue abounds as Ivan makes his return to Russia...at the behest of Nick Fury? Plus, Hercules and Iceman have their own comedy of errors thanks to malfunctioning security at Champions HQ! The villainous Swarm assembles his insect pack for the very first time.
description.12: Shot by Bullseye. Radar sense on the fritz. A threat pulling strings from the shadow. A severly hampered Daredevil will have to dig down deep to unravel the mystery.
description.13: While the Eternals are still part of the Uni-Mind, the Deviants launch a giant missile at the Celestials! Only Sprite remains to stop it, and he'll have to get help from an unlikely ally!
description.14: The Hulk battles the Quintronic Man with help from his pal Jim Wilson! Will these two neutralize the robotic menace?
description.15: Tony Stark must travel to China to rescue Kevin O'Brien, disguised as Iron Man, who had been captured by the Mandarin. But before he can defeat the Oriental Master himself, Iron Man must first face the Mandarin's Death Squad!
description.16: Omega gets unexpected aid in battling Blockbuster by the Foolkiller!
description.17: Thor and the Asgardians attempt to penetrate the Doomsday Star. Meanwhile, a mysterious onlooker looms outside Asgard.
description.18: Blade reaches a crossroads following the death of Deacon Frost. Will a new vampiric emergence shake the dust from his bones? A man's wife becomes afflicted with a rare form of vampirism, leaving Blade and Rachel Van Helsing with more questions than answers.
description.19: Reed, Sue and Ben set out to retrieve young Franklin who has been kidnapped along with Agatha Harkness. The team is in for a surprise however, when they enter the old, spooky mansion on Whisper Hill!
description.22: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.23: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.24: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.25: Carol Danvers--star journalist! The first issue of Carol's Woman Magazine is a success, but before she can even think about celebrating, she'll have to fight for her life against--GROTESK!
description.30: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.31: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.32: Odysseus, one of the great Greek warriors of the Trojan War, has not arrived home. His ship is blown off course by the vengeful sea god Poseidon, thus leading the hero into a series of awesome adventures that form a cornerstone of Western literature. Try the illustrated adaptation of Homer's epic quest today!
description.33: Thor side-by-side with the Guardians of the Galaxy! When the God of Thunder is mistakenly transported to the 31st century, he must team up with the Guardians to stop Korvac.
description.36: One man against a galactic empire: the mighty Star-Lord! (note: this contains the Star-Lord story only)
description.37: Discover the secret origin of Warrior Woman, the greatest Nazi nemesis of them all!
description.39: Rock and roll band Kiss have arrived to give advice to Howard the Duck! Although are they the real deal or demons from Winda's dark place? And all goes terribly wrong when Howard the Duck becomes the Duck of Satan!
description.45: Bullseye makes a televised threat against Daredevil, and our hero takes the bait. The only problem? Daredevil's radar senses are on the fritz after a golf ball to the head!
description.46: Johnny Blaze survives a deadly motorcycle crash by the skin of his teeth!
description.47: Every living Eternal comes together, transforming into a single entity. Its name? The Uni-Mind! will this new form help shed light on the Celestials' mysteries?
description.48: Can the Hulk save his friend Jim Wilson from the Constrictor? Meanwhile, Betty is gone in a flash- but has a new look and a new life!
description.49: It's Doomsday for the Armored Avenger, for the Mandarin has returned! And Iron Man is at his mercy! Plus: Madame Masque, an unlikely ally.
description.51: While Balder and Karnilla battle the brutish Executioner and the beautiful Enchantress, Thor joins the fray...fighting against his brother-in-arms!
description.52: The Forever Man versus the undead Dracula! Who will survive?
description.53: What if the Avengers had never been?
description.54: The X-Men have returned to the United States from Muir Island and have caught someone lurking in their headquarters.
description.55: It's a melee of miscreants when the Brute and the Scavenger go head-to-head! Will the FF, along with allies Thundra, Tigra, and the Impossible Man, manage to battle both beasts and complete their task in the Negative Zone?
description.59: Spider-Man finds himself in hot water after photos surface revealing him disposing of a Spider-Clone. Will Peter be clever enough to trick Jameson into believing the photos are frauds? Plus, Spider-Man encounters a new enclave of street villains, and this time they're armed with laser drills. The return of Doctor Faustus!
description.60: Wonder Man and The Vision are put on trial for their lives. Will their fellow teammates be able to bail them out of this one?
description.61: Now that Captain America is trapped, the next step in Red Skull's plan can begin!
description.62: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.63: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.64: Mar-Vell joins forces with the Avengers, just as Earth's Mightiest Heroes are ambushed by the SUPER-ADAPTAOID!
description.67: Mentallo and Fixer pull Deathlok from the future for their own nefarious deeds. Nick Fury and the Thing attempt to save Deathlok, but are soon sideswiped by Mentallo’s psychic powers. But why does Deathlok end up in chains, prisoner of the Fantastic Four?
description.69: The once-deadly Owl is looking to ascend to new heights of power.  Daredevil may have met his match with the all-new, all-deadly Owl.
description.71: Clash in the house of Stark! Ms. Marvel has to stop a shady radioactive truck from delivering its cargo, but the defender of the truck is an unexpected foe--the android Avenger known only as the Vision!
description.72: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.73: Please note that these digital editions collect material reprinted in Captain Britain Vol. 1: Birth of a Legend and Marvel Universe by Chris Claremont.
description.74: A tale of betrayal, revenge, and swashbuckling action as told in the mighty Marvel manner! An adaptation of Alexandre Dumas' classic.
description.75: All Eternals must return to Olympia! Zuras summons the entirety of his people, while the Russian military attacks a Celestial head-on!
description.76: It's steel versus solar flame! Sunfire, the living inferno, has returned! Plus: Find out why Iron Man must don his old armor!
description.77: Ruth, Amber, James-Michael, and Richard Roy are confronted with the fact that they have 24 hours to live - courtesy of the Foolkiller!
description.78: The Enchantress and the Executioner cause trouble in Asgard, while Grey Gargoyle and pirates vex Thor and the Asgardians!
description.79: Sure to be a best-seller comes Tomb of Dracula the novel! Truth is deadlier than fiction!
description.80: Counter-Earth Reed traps Johnny and Ben in the Negative Zone! Plus, it's more than a lover's quarrel when Sue confirms that this evil Reed has no regard for their son!
description.84: Spider-Man and Black Widow must work together to fight the Silver Samurai. It is a fight of wits and strength as they battle their way through New York. Is the Samurai only trying to defeat the Super Heroes, or did he come for something else?
description.85: While trying to rescue an American soldier, Cap is attacked by Master Man!
description.86: Howard wakes up in a jail cell and is set for a day in court? What crime are they accusing Howard of commiting?
description.87: In a near tussle to the death, Will O' the Wisp fights Spidey for an envelope he believes contains sensitive information. J. Jonah Jameson takes out his Spider-Slayer robot for another round, but soon realizes he is not equipped for battle. All is not as it seems with Spidey's new villain. Will Will O' the Wisp find the will to maintain his humanity?
description.88: Graviton has fallen off the deep end. Black Panther and Thor must perform a rescue mission to save their fellow Avengers. But will a mad-with-power Graviton have the upper hand...and final say?
description.89: Arnim Zola has captured Cap through the use of his abominable creation known as the Doughboy!
description.90: The Stranger's Null-Life Bomb is threatening to consume the Champions in its infernal core...not to mention all of Champions HQ! Darkstar makes a power play to save all of reality...but will her efforts be enough?
description.94: The Man-Bull makes an explosive prison break thanks to someone with a vendetta against Daredevil.  But can the Man Without Fear stop the Man-Bull from his quest to pay back his mysterious benefactor?
description.95: Grudge match in the cavern! While searching for answers about her discovery that she is Ms. Marvel, Carol is ambushed by Doomsday Man and the now Kree weapon-equipped Destructor! Can Carol survive a battle where she is both outnumbered AND outgunned?

3.text: Death has three faces! Featuring an appearance by the ferocious War-Yore!

6.text: After de-strapping himself from an atomic bomb, Luke Cage teams with local law enforcement to disarm Gideon’s plot to destroy Chicago!

12.text: Shot by Bullseye.  Radar sense on the fritz.  A threat pulling strings from the shadow.  A severly hampered Daredevil will have to dig down deep to unravel the mystery.

20.text: The final battle with Morbius takes place…but the Empathoid possesses one opponent!

25.text: Carol Danvers--star journalist! The first issue of Carol's Woman Magazine is a success, but before she can even think about celebrating, she'll have to fight for her life against--GROTESK!

26.text: Misty Knight is determined to pull off a sting operation on a drug pusher, but her methods may put her in more danger than she realizes. Alan Cavenaugh may revert back to his terroristic ways, putting him in direct conflict with pacifist-at-heart Iron Fist. Will the IRA rise again?

27.text: Nova has been encased in a bubble of pure energy! Can Nova save himself in time to save the world?

28.text: The Red Skull has a new weapon of mass destruction up his sleeve…and he’s itching to use it on the human population! Will Captain America and Namor be able to cooperate long enough to stop the Skull? Plus, the Shroud returns!

29.text: The Defenders decide to turn Jack Norriss over to S.H.I.E.L.D.  The team realizes too late that the “Nick Fury” they encountered is an imposter working for Scorpio! Moon Knight steps in to help locate Scorpio’s headquarters. Will the Defenders, with the help of Moon Knight, be able to withstand an army of Zodiac androids?

32.text: Odysseus, one of the great Greek warriors of the Trojan War, has not arrived home. His ship is blown off course by the vengeful sea god Poseidon, thus leading the hero into a series of awesome adventures that form a cornerstone of Western literature. Try the illustrated adaptation of Homer’s epic quest today!

34.text: A trip to London meets a watery fate! Ben Grimm and Alicia are pulled into an oceanic brawl as NAMOR battles with the PIRANHA!

38.text: While saving the Guardian of the Quadriverse, Doctor Strange is infected by a small demon!

40.text: The Kree unleash their deadliest warrior-assassin to eliminate the Royal Family!

41.text: Hoping to take the prize on Shang-Chi's head, minor criminal Demmy Marston hires a samurai to pursue the Master of Kung Fu!

44.text: Power Man is under the thumb of Gideon Mace! The mastermind has duped a woman named Burgundy, and Cage must show her the truth once and for all. Or else, Chicago may be ground zero to Mace’s next plot against the United States!

56.text: Spider-Man fears the worst when his web-shooters are damaged. The predicament worsens when Glory Grant is caught in the crosshairs of a possessed Morbius!

58.text: The psychic, vampiric Reavers of Arcturus want to feed on the life force of Starhawk--but not if the Guardians of the Galaxy have something to say about it!

64.text: Mar-Vell joins forces with the Avengers, just as Earth's Mightiest Heroes are ambushed by the SUPER-ADAPTAOID!

65.text: Blue blazes! Nova must save his family from a raging fire before tracking down Megaman.

66.text: In the caverns of King Solomon’s tomb! Perils abound lie in wait for Panther, Abner Little, and Princess Zanda. Will the trio find the second Brass Frog and restore King Solomon’s time machine?

67.text: Mentallo and Fixer pull Deathlok from the future for their own nefarious deeds. Nick Fury and the Thing attempt to save Deathlok, but are soon sideswiped by Mentallo’s psychic powers. But why does Deathlok end up in chains, prisoner of the Fantastic Four?

68.text: The Defenders attempt some R&R time, until Jack Norriss finds himself in hot water with Nick Fury! On her return to Avengers Mansion, Hellcat is attacked by an amnesiac Wonder-Man. What has pushed Wonder Man over the edge? And will the Defenders be able to bail Norriss out of his latest woes?

69.text: The once-deadly Owl is looking to ascend to new heights of power.  Daredevil may have met his match with the all-new, all-deadly Owl.

71.text: Clash in the house of Stark! Ms. Marvel has to stop a shady radioactive truck from delivering its cargo, but the defender of the truck is an unexpected foe--the android Avenger known only as the Vision!

74.text: A tale of betrayal, revenge, and swashbuckling action as told in the mighty Marvel manner! An adaptation of Alexandre Dumas’ classic.

81.text: Spidey recalls the time he teamed up with the Human Torch to defeat Morbius, the Living Vampire. Good thing Morbius' demise is set in stone…

91.text: Shang-Chi bumps into Rufus T. Hackstabber in Morocco.

93.text: Luke Cage vs. his most insidious foe yet…the IRS! Skipping town to protect his civilian identity, Power Man heads out for Chicago…but is intercepted by Gideon Mace en route!

94.text: The Man-Bull makes an explosive prison break thanks to someone with a vendetta against Daredevil.  But can the Man Without Fear stop the Man-Bull from his quest to pay back his mysterious benefactor?

95.text: Grudge match in the cavern! While searching for answers about her discovery that she is Ms. Marvel, Carol is ambushed by Doomsday Man and the now Kree weapon-equipped Destructor! Can Carol survive a battle where she is both outnumbered AND outgunned?

97.text: Captain America and Doctor Doom are shrunk down in size- and not in the way you think! An explosive battle ensues for the throne of Latveria. Will Doom reclaim his place as rightful monarch? Or will Prince Rudolfo continue his ruse over the Latverian people?

98.text: Clea has no memory of her ties to Doctor Strange. Will the Sorcerer Supreme be able to cure his disciple's amnesia?

99.text: Trespasser at Avengers Mansion! Captain America lunges into action when Iron Fist breaks into the Avengers’ HQ. But Cap has all the wrong ideas about Iron Fist; will Danny Rand be able to prove his innocence…and his heroism? Captain America and Iron Fist vs. the Wrecking Crew!
